A Quebec engineering firm poured thousands of dollars into federal Liberal and Conservative party coffers by getting employees to make donations then reimbursing them through fictitious expense claims, the Commissioner of Canada Elections revealed Friday.

In a compliance agreement reached four days before the federal election but only made public three weeks after it was reached, Dessau Inc admits that a former vice-president of a subsidiary, who has since died, solicited the political contributions between January 2005 and May
